text: Willy Tschopp (3 September 1905 – 5 November 1987) was a Swiss sprinter. He competed in the men's 100 metres at the 1928 Summer Olympics. He was born in Basel. Tschopp died on 5 November 1987 in Delémont at the age of 82.Willy Tschopp == References == Category:1905 births Category:1987 deaths Category:Olympians for Switzerland Category:Sprinters Category:Sportspeople from Basel
